                    <string key="text">Overview

The algorithm for generating the music in the app is a custom algorithm written for this app.

Chords

The chords are generated using a markov chain like algorithm and some preset patterns. It attempts to stay close to the main key.

Melody

The melody is based on chordscale theory. So each chord has a few scales that complement each chord. First, it creates a general outline and a rhythm, then tries to fill it in with scales and arpeggios. It also puts in a few approach notes.

The A section is considered the melody section, so is relatively stable and uses more normal scales. The B section is more of a solo section and uses faster rhythms as well as more chromatic sequences.

Rhythm

The rhythm section generally plays along with the chords as written. It tries to keep each chord as close to the previous as possible so will play any inversion necessary on each chord. It also will play A and B form for ii-V-I sequences.

Bass

The bass line is pretty simple. It always plays the root note on 1 and then plays an arpeggio or scale to the next root note.

Drums

Currently, the drums are incredibly simple. The just play the same measure on repeat. I'm not a drummer, and have very little knowledge of jazz drumming, so if you have some more ideas, please let me know.

Get In Touch

If you're interested in more about the algorithm, get in touch. You can send me an email with the feedback option in the menu.</string>
